00:17:13.130 --> 00:17:17.460
Besides, the Speed Stars had
nothing to do with this...

00:17:17.460 --> 00:17:21.000
You don't think we can
convince Takumi to race?

00:17:21.000 --> 00:17:25.370
No. I know him better than anyone,
and he'll never do it...

00:17:25.370 --> 00:17:29.180
He hates being forced into things

00:17:29.180 --> 00:17:32.050
or having to follow others' orders.

00:17:32.050 --> 00:17:34.210
He looks real mellow,

00:17:34.210 --> 00:17:37.580
but once he says something,
there's no changing his mind...

00:17:37.580 --> 00:17:42.320
<i>Stubborn... just like his father.</i>

00:17:42.320 --> 00:17:46.330
He doesn't understand why
racers have to accept challenges.

00:17:46.330 --> 00:17:49.430
The whole system offends him.

00:17:49.430 --> 00:17:52.900
When someone tries to force
him to do something, he snaps.

00:17:52.900 --> 00:17:54.740
One time in eleventh grade, he flipped out

00:17:54.740 --> 00:17:57.540
and beat up a group of
seniors after soccer practice.

00:17:57.540 --> 00:18:00.200
What?! Takumi did that?

00:18:13.650 --> 00:18:17.320
Boss, I finished cleaning up outside.

00:18:17.320 --> 00:18:19.230
Thanks.

00:18:19.230 --> 00:18:21.630
No problem. See you tomorrow, then.

00:18:21.630 --> 00:18:23.160
Takumi!

00:18:23.160 --> 00:18:25.470
Come and have a seat.

00:18:25.470 --> 00:18:27.130
Okay...

00:18:29.140 --> 00:18:33.240
You know, I overheard some talk.

00:18:33.240 --> 00:18:35.580
You're going to race an R32 tonight?

00:18:35.580 --> 00:18:37.180
What? I'm...

00:18:37.180 --> 00:18:40.880
Don't do it, Takumi. That guy's bad news.

00:18:40.880 --> 00:18:42.750
Uh... No, I wasn't...

00:18:42.750 --> 00:18:46.890
No, no. I know what you're going to say.

00:18:46.890 --> 00:18:49.860
I've known everything from the beginning.

00:18:49.860 --> 00:18:54.060
I know it wasn't your decision to take this race.

00:18:54.060 --> 00:18:56.200
Itsuki was the one who screwed
up and accepted it, right?

00:18:56.200 --> 00:18:57.230
Yeah...

00:18:57.230 --> 00:19:00.270
You know, you're too nice sometimes.

00:19:00.270 --> 00:19:03.870
You gotta stop bailing your
friends out all the time.

00:19:03.870 --> 00:19:07.210
Trust me. Whatever you do,
don't race that R32.

00:19:07.210 --> 00:19:09.480
There's a lot you don't know about cars.

00:19:09.480 --> 00:19:13.510
Do you even know what an R32 can do?

00:19:13.510 --> 00:19:16.810
Is an R32 that amazing?

00:19:19.350 --> 00:19:21.790
<i>Gotcha! He took the bait...</i>

00:19:21.790 --> 00:19:24.160
It's beyond amazing.

00:19:24.160 --> 00:19:26.330
That car's in a class by itself!

00:19:26.330 --> 00:19:28.200
Its driving system combines everything good

00:19:28.200 --> 00:19:31.030
about FR and four-wheel drive.

00:19:31.030 --> 00:19:34.300
It's a beast!

00:19:34.300 --> 00:19:37.070
An Eight-Six or GT-R is no match for it.

00:19:37.070 --> 00:19:39.340
If the driver was an amateur,
you'd have a chance,

00:19:39.340 --> 00:19:42.210
but you're up against a famous racer, right?

00:19:42.210 --> 00:19:44.510
<i>Dad didn't tell me this.</i>

00:19:44.510 --> 00:19:47.710
<i>He said it'd be a close race.</i>

00:19:47.710 --> 00:19:49.150
Hey.

00:19:49.150 --> 00:19:51.050
You with me?

00:19:51.050 --> 00:19:55.820
You just became famous yourself
by beating that team from Akagi.

00:19:55.820 --> 00:19:58.490
You shouldn't ruin your name so fast...

00:19:58.490 --> 00:20:02.260
It's not wise to go up against someone
you have no chance of defeating.

00:20:02.260 --> 00:20:04.000
You hear me?

00:20:04.000 --> 00:20:06.200
Since your opponent's driving an R32,

00:20:06.200 --> 00:20:08.570
no one would call you
a coward for backing out.

00:20:09.570 --> 00:20:11.510
<i>A coward?!</i>

00:20:14.910 --> 00:20:17.410
Boss...

00:20:17.410 --> 00:20:21.450
Thanks for the warning...

00:20:21.450 --> 00:20:27.220
...but I could care less
about my fame as a racer.

00:20:30.560 --> 00:20:33.260
So you aren't going to back down?

00:20:33.260 --> 00:20:36.030
No.

00:20:36.030 --> 00:20:38.400
Hearing about how amazing that car is

00:20:38.400 --> 00:20:42.530
has only made me want to see it in action.

00:20:44.770 --> 00:20:49.400
I'm not afraid of an R32 or any other car.

00:20:53.650 --> 00:20:55.820
Whew!

00:20:55.820 --> 00:20:59.880
He's exactly like his father...

00:21:03.860 --> 00:21:05.720 line:50 %
"Temporarily Closed

00:21:03.860 --> 00:21:05.720 line:50 %
Fujiwara Tofu Shop"

00:21:07.060 --> 00:21:09.600
Temporarily closed?

00:21:09.600 --> 00:21:11.730
Dad never said anything about this.

00:21:11.730 --> 00:21:15.840
How's he going to make
money if the shop's closed?

00:21:15.840 --> 00:21:18.170
Oh, no! The car!

00:21:20.670 --> 00:21:23.580
If he went out drinking, I'm really in trouble.

00:21:23.580 --> 00:21:27.880
He won't be back until morning!

00:21:27.880 --> 00:21:30.420
I can't do anything without a car.

00:21:30.420 --> 00:21:33.790
I should have asked to borrow it this morning!

00:21:35.590 --> 00:21:37.860
Look at the crowd!

00:21:37.860 --> 00:21:41.560
There's even more people out
tonight than at the Akagi race!

00:21:41.560 --> 00:21:45.230
Why did so many people come tonight?

00:21:45.230 --> 00:21:47.930
You know they're not here to see the R32.

00:21:47.930 --> 00:21:50.940
Yeah, they want to see that Eight-Six drift!

00:21:50.940 --> 00:21:56.980
They say he barrels through
corners as if they're straightaways!

00:21:56.980 --> 00:21:59.110
I can't wait to see this!

00:21:59.110 --> 00:22:02.180
Oh... I see...

00:22:02.180 --> 00:22:08.490
Uh, if he happens to show up,
could you ask him to call home?

00:22:08.490 --> 00:22:10.350
Thanks...

00:22:13.730 --> 00:22:17.000
It's no use... I can't find him...

00:22:17.000 --> 00:22:18.400
Damn!

00:22:18.400 --> 00:22:22.360
Where the hell are you?!
Give me back my Eight-Six!

00:22:43.760 --> 00:22:46.460
<i>My pride says you gotta be wild and tough</i>

00:22:46.460 --> 00:22:48.530
<i>So no one intervenes</i>

00:22:48.530 --> 00:22:50.060
<i>Never stop, I don't want to stop</i>

00:22:50.060 --> 00:22:52.130
<i>Even if you cry because of a sacrificed love</i>

00:22:52.130 --> 00:22:53.930
<i>Aim for the peak, sweep the winding street</i>

00:22:53.930 --> 00:22:56.140
<i>Beep beep! The warning chime is so cheap!</i>

00:22:56.140 --> 00:22:57.600
<i>The sheep should clear the road</i>

00:22:57.600 --> 00:23:00.040
<i>'Cuz I'm never gonna stop, streak my dream</i>

00:23:00.040 --> 00:23:03.910
<i>Easy motivation is total stimulation</i>

00:23:03.910 --> 00:23:07.980
<i>You tried to escape,</i>
<i>but anywhere is a safety zone</i>

00:23:07.980 --> 00:23:11.990
<i>Something is within your grasp</i>
<i>and something is forgotten</i>

00:23:11.990 --> 00:23:15.920
<i>Even if the world ends it will never change</i>

00:23:15.920 --> 00:23:24.000
<i>Beasty shout, no one can touch you</i>

00:23:24.000 --> 00:23:31.370
<i>Cross over now to the time of an intense dream</i>

00:23:31.370 --> 00:23:35.410
<i>Rage your dream, split the darkness</i>

00:23:35.410 --> 00:23:37.380
<i>Like a streak to the peak</i>

00:23:37.380 --> 00:23:43.520
<i>Erase the freezing darkness worldwide</i>

00:23:43.520 --> 00:23:47.390
<i>Rage your dream, and open the road</i>

00:23:47.390 --> 00:23:50.060
<i>Di-ding down, another round never slow down</i>

00:23:50.060 --> 00:23:52.060
<i>A point 01 second knockdown</i>

00:23:52.060 --> 00:23:54.260
<i>Reverberations left behind,</i>
<i>disappear to the next town</i>

00:23:54.260 --> 00:23:56.100
<i>The losers are left in the dust</i>

00:23:56.100 --> 00:23:58.060
<i>Let's ignore the constraints of logic</i>

00:23:58.060 --> 00:24:00.030
<i>'Cause they're a pain</i>

00:24:00.030 --> 00:24:02.170
<i>A streaker runs naked across the street</i>

00:24:02.170 --> 00:24:03.370
<i>Something they would know</i>

00:24:03.370 --> 00:24:07.410
<i>Rage your dream,</i>
<i>continue on the unending road</i>

00:24:07.410 --> 00:24:11.410
<i>Don't look back on your love or your past</i>

00:24:11.410 --> 00:24:15.480
<i>Go forward and you'll shine brightly</i>

00:24:15.480 --> 00:24:20.550
<i>Rage your dream, you're living in the now</i>

00:24:26.590 --> 00:24:28.500
<i>Kenji, who do you think will win</i>

00:24:28.500 --> 00:24:32.170
<i>this battle Itsuki got us into,</i>
<i>the R32 or the Eight-Six?</i>

00:24:32.170 --> 00:24:34.400
<i>Of course, I'd like to say the Eight-Six...</i>

00:24:34.400 --> 00:24:38.270
<i>...but I don't know if even Takumi</i>
<i>can beat a GT-R, the fastest domestic.</i>

00:24:38.270 --> 00:24:41.270
<i>The biggest question is if</i>
<i>Takumi will even come to race!</i>

00:24:41.270 --> 00:24:44.240
<i>If he doesn't show up,</i>
<i>then Kenji will once more...</i>

00:24:44.240 --> 00:24:45.850
<i>Don't say it!</i>

00:24:45.850 --> 00:24:48.380
<i>Next time on Initial D, "Time's Almost Up!"</i>

00:24:48.380 --> 00:24:51.450
<i>Takumi, please get here soon!</i>

00:24:51.450 --> 00:24:53.350
<i>Don't miss it!</i>